#: ../../language/error_codes/E0005.md:1
msgid "E0005"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0005.md:3
msgid "Warning name: `unused_type_variable`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0005.md:5
msgid "Unused generic type variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0005.md:7
msgid ""
"In some cases, using types with unused generic type variables will make "
"it impossible for the type checker to infer the type of the unused "
"variable, leading to [E0013](./E0013.md). This might lead to cryptic "
"error messages, even unexpected runtime behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0005.md:12
msgid "Erroneous example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0005.md:14
msgid ""
"///|\n"
"priv struct Foo[T] {\n"
"  bar : Int\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"///|\n"
"test {\n"
"  let bar : Foo[Int] = { bar: 42 }\n"
"  inspect(bar.bar, content=\"42\")\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0005.md:18
msgid "Suggestion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0005.md:20
msgid "If the type variable is indeed useless, remove the unused type variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0005.md:22
msgid ""
"\n"
"///|\n"
"priv struct Foo {\n"
"  bar : Int\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0005.md:28
msgid ""
"If you wish to keep the type variable, you can use `_` to indicate that "
"the type variable is intentionally unused."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0005.md:31
msgid ""
"\n"
"///|\n"
"priv struct Foo2[_] {\n"
"  bar2 : Int\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

